From d44d29fff3d107b21cc80c721b981071aa2307d5 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Josua Mayer <josua@solid-run.com>
Date: Mon, 4 May 2026 12:57:57 +0200
Subject: [PATCH] net: dpaa2-mac-standalone: fix netdev registration race
 condition

The standalone DPAA2 MAC driver registers the netdev during probe before
allocating the MC portal. In the remove path, it unregisters the netdev
only after freeing the portal.

This creates a race condition where netdev_ops or phylink workers can
attempt to access the portal (mc_io) during the windows when the netdev
is visible but the portal is NULL or invalid.

This issue is specifically exposed on PREEMPT_RT kernels, where threaded
interrupt handlers and workqueues (like phylink_resolve) can be scheduled
to run immediately after registration or just before unregistration
finishes, leading to a NULL pointer dereference.

Reorder the registration to be the last step in probe and the
unregistration to be the first step in remove. This ensures that the
communication portal is fully established before the netdev is visible
and remains valid until the netdev is fully unregistered.

